From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Entrpi <entrpi@proton.me>
Date: Sun, 30 Nov 2025 22:05:36 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: dts: cix: Fix USB controller interrupt cell count

The GIC interrupt controller requires 4 cells per interrupt specifier,
but the USB controller nodes only specified 3 cells. Add the missing
4th cell (PPI affinity, set to 0 for SPI interrupts) to all USB
controller interrupt definitions.

This fixes device tree warnings and ensures proper interrupt routing
for all USB controllers (usbss_0 through usbhs_3).
